Retail Dynamics: In Ireland, traditional retailers like Dunnes Stores, Penneys (Primark), and Marks & Spencer remain popular for casual wear. However, international fast-fashion brands such as H&M and Zara also dominate the landscape. Irish consumers tend to favor multi-brand stores that offer variety and price flexibility, making it easier for smaller businesses to compete if they offer niche products or personalized services(
